    grammar: { title: `Articles — a, an, the, or nothing`, content: `Articles are one of the trickiest parts of English. 'A/an' = indefinite, first mention or one of many: 'I saw a great movie'. 'The' = specific, already mentioned or unique: 'The movie was amazing' (the one we're talking about). No article with: general plural nouns ('I love dogs'), uncountable nouns in general ('Music is beautiful'), names of most countries ('France, England') but not 'the USA, the UK'. Tricky cases: 'I went to school' (general activity) vs 'I went to the school' (specific building). 'She's in hospital' (British English, meaning receiving care) vs 'She's in the hospital' (American English, the building).` },
